    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nails that have a broad head with a flat, rectangular shank and spear-like point. They differ from "hurdle nails" in that gate nails are usually stouter and made in various lengths.</Note_Text>
